Here's a minimal API endpoint handling multipart form uploads with multiple images and a description:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise the max request body size to 50 MB
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 50 * 1024 * 1024);

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Read the multipart form; set the value-length and file-length limits
    var form = await request.ReadFormAsync(new FormOptions
    {
        MultipartBodyLengthLimit = 50 * 1024 * 1024,
        ValueLengthLimit        = 1024 * 1024
    });

    var description = form["description"].ToString();
    var files       = form.Files.GetFiles("images");

    if (files.Count == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("No files uploaded.");

    var saved = new List<string>();

    foreach (var file in files)
    {
        if (!file.ContentType.StartsWith("image/"))
            return Results.BadRequest($"'{file.FileName}' is not an image.");

        var path = Path.Combine("uploads", $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{Path.GetExtension(file.FileName)}");
        Directory.CreateDirectory("uploads");

        await using var stream = File.Create(path);
        await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

        saved.Add(path);
    }

    return Results.Ok(new { description, uploadedFiles = saved });
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // required for minimal APIs accepting form data without a token

app.Run();
```

**Key points:**

- **Kestrel limit** — `MaxRequestBodySize` must be raised from the 30 MB default, otherwise the server rejects the request before your code runs.
- **`FormOptions`** — `MultipartBodyLengthLimit` caps what `ReadFormAsync` will accept per part.
- **`DisableAntiforgery()`** — minimal APIs enforce antiforgery on form bindings by default; disable it for API-style endpoints (or wire up tokens if needed).
- Form fields are read via `form["description"]`; files via `form.Files.GetFiles("images")` (matches the HTML `name` attribute).

**Example `curl` call:**

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:5000/upload \
  -F "description=My vacation photos" \
  -F "images=@photo1.jpg" \
  -F "images=@photo2.png"
```
